    "created_at": "2015-10-14T09:48:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-14T09:48:19Z",
    "body": "Hi @zcbenz \nI found app.getLocale() have some wired behavior.\nUnder OS X, app.getLocale() return different value at \"different context\".\nUnder Windows, app.getLocale() always return correct value.\nFor example:\n\n``` javascript\nvar app = require('app');\nconsole.log(app.getLocale());    // See en-US in OS X, it's wrong, but correct in Windows\napp.on('ready', function() {\n  console.log(app.getLocale());  // See zh-CN\n});\n```\n\nNot tested in linux.\nIs this by design?\n"
